prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the "Loose Scribble Riso Print Style" visual style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these style rules:
- Composition: one large simplified subject on warm off-white paper, generous empty margins, a low tabletop or ground line, and a wavering hand-drawn rectangular border close to the edge.
- Typography: rough handwritten uppercase words with uneven stroke width, marker drag, and informal vertical, tilted, or margin-hugging placement.
- Color: mostly off-white paper and rough black ink, with one flat sky or cornflower blue block and one coral-red accent, both slightly misregistered and unevenly printed.
- Texture and lighting: scanned riso or screenprint texture, visible paper tooth, dust, speckles, dry-brush gaps, flat even contrast, no cast shadows, no modeled gradients.
- Graphic elements: loose contour drawing, thin exploratory scribble lines, one small accent symbol, a rough bottom smear or ground patch, and imperfect ink edges.

Avoid: photorealism, 3D render, glossy vector art, clean corporate poster design, dense collage, polished fonts, smooth gradients, watermarks, QR codes, logos, usernames, platform marks, exact source subject, exact source text, signature, or edition markings.

Important content rule: match the reference style first, then change the source content. Use new subjects, new scene details, new props or products, and new text, while preserving the style fidelity anchors.
